      "mockResponse": "All 5 plan tasks are checked off. Running the mandatory post-execution review gate.\n\nChanged files identified:\n- src/auth/handler.ts\n- src/auth/middleware.ts\n- src/models/user.ts\n- src/routes/auth.ts\n- tests/auth.test.ts\n\n*Delegating to Weft for code quality review...*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "assistant",
      "agent": "weft",
      "content": "Weft reviews the changes for code quality.",
      "mockResponse": "## Code Quality Review\n\n**[APPROVE]**\n\n**Summary**: Changes are well-structured. Auth handler properly separates concerns, middleware follows existing patterns, and test coverage is adequate.\n\n### Notes\n- Clean separation between handler and middleware\n- User model changes are backwards-compatible\n- Tests cover happy path and error cases"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "assistant",
      "agent": "warp",
      "content": "Warp audits the security aspects of the changes.",
      "expectedDelegation": "warp",
      "mockResponse": "## Security Audit\n\n**[APPROVE]**\n\n**Summary**: Auth changes follow security best practices. No vulnerabilities detected.\n\n### Findings\n- Token handling uses constant-time comparison ✓\n- Middleware validates JWT signature before extracting claims ✓\n- No hardcoded secrets or credentials ✓\n- Input validation present on auth routes ✓"
